WHO   — Brodie's Comic Gospel — the worldview · the Stan Lee scene
WHAT  — The lens of the movie: everything filtered through superheroes, escalators, and the deep questions Stan Lee is summoned to answer.
WHERE — MLR · Mallrats (1995)  Framework inputs: Mallrats (1995, dir. Kevin Smith, Gramercy/View Askew); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because Mallrats is, under the gags, a sincere argument that this stuff matters — and the gospel is the argument.
HOW   — By treating fandom as faith, decades before the world agreed that it was.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Comics aren't a distraction from life — they're the operating manual. Ask Stan Lee; I did.

